description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen to recruit a motivated and experienced Team Secretary to join our busy team (30 hours per week), You must have excellent organisational skills, have a flexible approach, be able to work on your own initiative and be a team player.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The main responsibilities of the role will be to provide full administrative support to the clinical team, and the medical secretary based within the team. Excellent communication and customer care skills are essential as well as the necessity to maintain confidentiality at all times.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must have a good education, secretarial skills, sound IT knowledge and experience, with competency in Microsoft Office packages being essential. Experience of working in a clinical area is desirable. The ability to communicate effectively with patients who may experience communication difficulties is an essential requirement of the role. Also required is a methodical and flexible approach to work, good team working skills, the willingness to perform repetitive tasks accurately and to remain calm under pressure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should hold NVQ level 3 in Business &amp; Administration, or have a willingness to work towards the award&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Faye Jackson, Team Manager: &lt;/strong&gt;01765 632944 or 07717355967. Email: faye.jackson1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Beverly Mcnally &lt;strong&gt;Medical Secretary&lt;/strong&gt; : 01765 632944&lt;/p&gt;
